{\"sentence\": \"In late 2020 and early 2021, 23 elite Chinese swimmers tested positive for trimetazidine, known as TMZ, a heart medication classified among the most serious category of performance-enhancing drugs.\", \"from\": 324, \"to\": 521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 362, \"end\": 369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999658282344805, \"rank\": 3.220479488678925e-05, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 423, \"end\": 426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3793586733782727e-19, \"text\": \"TMZ\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"trimetazidine\", \"from\": 399, \"to\": 412}, {\"ngram\": \"a heart medication\", \"from\": 428, \"to\": 446}, {\"ngram\": \"the most serious category\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 489}, {\"ngram\": \"performance-enhancing drugs\", \"from\": 493, \"to\": 520}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But they continued to compete, including at theTokyo Olympicsin 2021, after the China Anti-Doping Agency (Chinada) determined all 23 cases were the result of contaminated food at Huayang Holiday Hotel in Shijiazhuang, where the swimmers were staying.\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 773, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 603, \"end\": 608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999788688964895, \"rank\": 2.1130857107042806e-05, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 702, \"end\": 709, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhengzhou\", \"score\": 0.9999999956553438, \"rank\": 4.344530534347782e-09, \"text\": \"Huayang\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhengzhou\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhengzhou\"}, {\"begin\": 710, \"end\": 723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holiday_Hotel\", \"score\": 0.9999999996157385, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Holiday Hotel\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holiday_Hotel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holiday_Hotel\"}, {\"begin\": 727, \"end\": 739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shijiazhuang\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.412511144554084e-24, \"text\": \"Shijiazhuang\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shijiazhuang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shijiazhuang\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theTokyo Olympicsin\", \"from\": 567, \"to\": 586}, {\"ngram\": \"Chinada\", \"from\": 629, \"to\": 636}, {\"ngram\": \"all 23 cases\", \"from\": 649, \"to\": 661}, {\"ngram\": \"the result\", \"from\": 667, \"to\": 677}, {\"ngram\": \"contaminated food\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 698}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimmers\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 759}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes who had tested positive went on to claim three gold medals inTokyo, including Wang Shun, who became just the second Chinese man to win an individual swimming gold in the 200m individual medley.\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 977, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 862, \"end\": 871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Shun\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wang Shun\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Shun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Shun\"}, {\"begin\": 900, \"end\": 907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999658282344805, \"rank\": 3.220479488678925e-05, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletes\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 783}, {\"ngram\": \"three gold medals inTokyo\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 850}, {\"ngram\": \"an individual swimming gold\", \"from\": 919, \"to\": 946}, {\"ngram\": \"the 200m individual medley\", \"from\": 950, \"to\": 976}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Qin Haiyang, expected to beAdam Peaty'sclosest rival in the 100m breaststroke, also tested positive in 2021, alongside 12 other Chinese swimmers competing inParis.\", \"from\": 979, \"to\": 1142, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 979, \"end\": 990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_Haiyang\", \"score\": 0.9999938624998401, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Qin Haiyang\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_Haiyang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_Haiyang\"}, {\"begin\": 1107, \"end\": 1114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999658282344805, \"rank\": 3.220479488678925e-05, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Peaty'sclosest rival\", \"from\": 1011, \"to\": 1031}, {\"ngram\": \"the 100m breaststroke\", \"from\": 1035, \"to\": 1056}, {\"ngram\": \"inParis\", \"from\": 1134, \"to\": 1141}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's everything you need to know about the row which could overshadow these Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1144, \"to\": 1236, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1161}, {\"ngram\": \"the row\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1192}, {\"ngram\": \"these Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1235}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While at a New Year's event in Shijiazhuang, a city of 11 million people not far from Beijing, 60 tests were conducted on 39 swimmers.\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1372, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1269, \"end\": 1281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shijiazhuang\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.412511144554084e-24, \"text\": \"Shijiazhuang\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shijiazhuang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shijiazhuang\"}, {\"begin\": 1324, \"end\": 1331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999976569077103, \"rank\": 2.3402782240355773e-05, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a New Year's event\", \"from\": 1247, \"to\": 1265}, {\"ngram\": \"a city\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1289}, {\"ngram\": \"11 million people\", \"from\": 1293, \"to\": 1310}, {\"ngram\": \"60 tests\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1341}, {\"ngram\": \"39 swimmers\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These 60 tests produced 28 positive samples from 23 of the competitors, all for TMZ.\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1458, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These 60 tests\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1388}, {\"ngram\": \"28 positive samples\", \"from\": 1398, \"to\": 1417}, {\"ngram\": \"the competitors\", \"from\": 1429, \"to\": 1444}, {\"ngram\": \"TMZ\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1457}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 61-page Chinada report said investigators discovered traces of TMZ in spice containers, cooktop vents and sink drains in the team hotel, although it has never been established how that was transmitted to the swimmers.\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1681, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 61-page Chinada report\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1486}, {\"ngram\": \"investigators\", \"from\": 1492, \"to\": 1505}, {\"ngram\": \"traces\", \"from\": 1517, \"to\": 1523}, {\"ngram\": \"TMZ\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1530}, {\"ngram\": \"spice containers\", \"from\": 1534, \"to\": 1550}, {\"ngram\": \"cooktop vents\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1565}, {\"ngram\": \"sink drains\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1581}, {\"ngram\": \"the team hotel\", \"from\": 1585, \"to\": 1599}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimmers\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1680}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wada general counsel Ross Wenzel has said Chinada \\\"did not hypothesise\\\" why trace amounts of a prescription heart medication were found all over the kitchen of the team hotel.\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1858, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1704, \"end\": 1708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ross_Geller\", \"score\": 0.9999988657929928, \"rank\": 1.1341302010909422e-06, \"text\": \"Ross\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ross_Geller\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ross_Geller\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Chinada\", \"from\": 1725, \"to\": 1732}, {\"ngram\": \"why trace amounts\", \"from\": 1755, \"to\": 1772}, {\"ngram\": \"a prescription heart medication\", \"from\": 1776, \"to\": 1807}, {\"ngram\": \"the kitchen\", \"from\": 1828, \"to\": 1839}, {\"ngram\": \"the team hotel\", \"from\": 1843, \"to\": 1857}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All positive samples should be sent toWadaandWorld Aquatics(then known as Fina) immediately, but these tests were frozen for two and a half months before being delivered to Wada, reportedly due to the Covid-19 pandemic.\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 2079, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"All positive samples\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 1880}, {\"ngram\": \"toWadaandWorld\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 1910}, {\"ngram\": \"Fina\", \"from\": 1934, \"to\": 1938}, {\"ngram\": \"these tests\", \"from\": 1957, \"to\": 1968}, {\"ngram\": \"Wada\", \"from\": 2033, \"to\": 2037}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The anti-doping body chose not to act further having \\\"carefully reviewed the decision\\\" and spoken to external lawyers and scientists.\", \"from\": 2081, \"to\": 2214, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The anti-doping body\", \"from\": 2081, \"to\": 2101}, {\"ngram\": \"the decision\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2166}, {\"ngram\": \"external lawyers\", \"from\": 2182, \"to\": 2198}, {\"ngram\": \"scientists\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2213}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 23 swimmers then competed in Tokyo and the positive results only became public knowledge in April this year, after an investigation byThe New York Timesand German news outletARD.\", \"from\": 2216, \"to\": 2398, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2249, \"end\": 2254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.3195541235521697e-13, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2358, \"end\": 2366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999992264748, \"rank\": 7.612909535923657e-10, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 2376, \"end\": 2382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.9468709251070079, \"rank\": 0.04450423457816502, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 23 swimmers\", \"from\": 2216, \"to\": 2231}, {\"ngram\": \"the positive results\", \"from\": 2259, \"to\": 2279}, {\"ngram\": \"public knowledge\", \"from\": 2292, \"to\": 2308}, {\"ngram\": \"April\", \"from\": 2312, \"to\": 2317}, {\"ngram\": \"an investigation\", \"from\": 2335, \"to\": 2351}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As Wada came to the conclusion there was no wrongdoing, president Witold Banka said: \\\"It's a question about whether you want or not to expose the innocent athletes, right?\\\"\", \"from\": 2400, \"to\": 2572, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2466, \"end\": 2472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vytautas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.708086535261024e-15, \"text\": \"Witold\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vytautas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vytautas\"}, {\"begin\": 2473, \"end\": 2478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangka_Island\", \"score\": 0.9048453665577332, \"rank\": 0.10475423378918296, \"text\": \"Banka\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangka_Island\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangka_Island\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wada\", \"from\": 2403, \"to\": 2407}, {\"ngram\": \"the conclusion\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2430}, {\"ngram\": \"no wrongdoing\", \"from\": 2441, \"to\": 2454}, {\"ngram\": \"a question\", \"from\": 2491, \"to\": 2501}, {\"ngram\": \"the innocent athletes\", \"from\": 2542, \"to\": 2563}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Timesreported that World Aquatics only shared the evidence with Dr Jordi Segura, chairman of its doping control Review Board - none of the rest of the committee were informed of the positive tests.\", \"from\": 2574, \"to\": 2775, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2651, \"end\": 2657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pancho_Segura\", \"score\": 0.9992347761258328, \"rank\": 0.000765809890392718, \"text\": \"Segura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pancho_Segura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pancho_Segura\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Timesreported\", \"from\": 2574, \"to\": 2591}, {\"ngram\": \"World Aquatics\", \"from\": 2597, \"to\": 2611}, {\"ngram\": \"the evidence\", \"from\": 2624, \"to\": 2636}, {\"ngram\": \"chairman\", \"from\": 2659, \"to\": 2667}, {\"ngram\": \"its doping control\", \"from\": 2671, \"to\": 2689}, {\"ngram\": \"Review Board\", \"from\": 2690, \"to\": 2702}, {\"ngram\": \"none\", \"from\": 2705, \"to\": 2709}, {\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 2713, \"to\": 2721}, {\"ngram\": \"the committee\", \"from\": 2725, \"to\": 2738}, {\"ngram\": \"the positive tests\", \"from\": 2756, \"to\": 2774}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This was despite international anti-doping officials providing Wada with intelligence appearing to show a cover-up of doping by Chinese swimmers, including an email exchange between a Chinese official and a senior world swimming official suggesting a violation may have taken place.\", \"from\": 2777, \"to\": 3059, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2905, \"end\": 2912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999658282344805, \"rank\": 3.220479488678925e-05, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2961, \"end\": 2968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999658282344805, \"rank\": 3.220479488678925e-05, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"international anti-doping officials\", \"from\": 2794, \"to\": 2829}, {\"ngram\": \"Wada\", \"from\": 2840, \"to\": 2844}, {\"ngram\": \"intelligence\", \"from\": 2850, \"to\": 2862}, {\"ngram\": \"a cover-up\", \"from\": 2881, \"to\": 2891}, {\"ngram\": \"doping\", \"from\": 2895, \"to\": 2901}, {\"ngram\": \"an email exchange\", \"from\": 2933, \"to\": 2950}, {\"ngram\": \"a senior world swimming official\", \"from\": 2982, \"to\": 3014}, {\"ngram\": \"a violation\", \"from\": 3026, \"to\": 3037}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 3053, \"to\": 3058}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ARDalso revealed recently that there is evidence not all athletes were staying in the same hotel, while some of those who tested positive did not find out until the investigation was published in April.\", \"from\": 3061, \"to\": 3263, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ARDalso\", \"from\": 3061, \"to\": 3068}, {\"ngram\": \"evidence\", \"from\": 3101, \"to\": 3109}, {\"ngram\": \"not all athletes\", \"from\": 3110, \"to\": 3126}, {\"ngram\": \"the same hotel\", \"from\": 3143, \"to\": 3157}, {\"ngram\": \"the investigation\", \"from\": 3222, \"to\": 3239}, {\"ngram\": \"April\", \"from\": 3257, \"to\": 3262}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A further independent investigation concluded in July that Wada had not shown bias in their handling of the case, despite their senior director of science and medicine Olivier Rabin having \\\"doubts about the reality of contamination as described by the Chinese authorities.\\\"\", \"from\": 3265, \"to\": 3538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3517, \"end\": 3524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999658282344805, \"rank\": 3.220479488678925e-05, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A further independent investigation\", \"from\": 3265, \"to\": 3300}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 3314, \"to\": 3318}, {\"ngram\": \"Wada\", \"from\": 3324, \"to\": 3328}, {\"ngram\": \"bias\", \"from\": 3343, \"to\": 3347}, {\"ngram\": \"their handling\", \"from\": 3351, \"to\": 3365}, {\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 3369, \"to\": 3377}, {\"ngram\": \"their senior director\", \"from\": 3387, \"to\": 3408}, {\"ngram\": \"science\", \"from\": 3412, \"to\": 3419}, {\"ngram\": \"medicine\", \"from\": 3424, \"to\": 3432}, {\"ngram\": \"Olivier Rabin\", \"from\": 3433, \"to\": 3446}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"doubts\", \"from\": 3454, \"to\": 3461}, {\"ngram\": \"the reality\", \"from\": 3468, \"to\": 3479}, {\"ngram\": \"contamination\", \"from\": 3483, \"to\": 3496}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet Mr Rabin said he \\\"saw no solution than to accept it\\\" as Wada was \\\"not in a position to disprove\\\" Chinada's version of events.\", \"from\": 3540, \"to\": 3669, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Mr Rabin\", \"from\": 3544, \"to\": 3552}, {\"ngram\": \"no solution\", \"from\": 3566, \"to\": 3577}, {\"ngram\": \"Wada\", \"from\": 3600, \"to\": 3604}, {\"ngram\": \"a position\", \"from\": 3617, \"to\": 3627}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\" Chinada's version\", \"from\": 3639, \"to\": 3658}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 3662, \"to\": 3668}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the bodies who has given Wada allegations of Chinese doping on multiple occasions in the past four years is the US anti-doping body Usada.\", \"from\": 3671, \"to\": 3816, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3723, \"end\": 3730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999658282344805, \"rank\": 3.220479488678925e-05, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 3790, \"end\": 3792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.7564362529624433, \"rank\": 0.32198163618250886, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the bodies\", \"from\": 3678, \"to\": 3688}, {\"ngram\": \"Wada\", \"from\": 3703, \"to\": 3707}, {\"ngram\": \"allegations\", \"from\": 3708, \"to\": 3719}, {\"ngram\": \"multiple occasions\", \"from\": 3741, \"to\": 3759}, {\"ngram\": \"the past four years\", \"from\": 3763, \"to\": 3782}, {\"ngram\": \"Usada\", \"from\": 3810, \"to\": 3815}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Usada CEO Travis Tygart toldTheNew York Times: \\\"This appears to be a devastating stab in the back of clean athletes and a deep betrayal of all the athletes who compete fairly and follow the rules.\", \"from\": 3818, \"to\": 4014, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3828, \"end\": 3841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Travis Tygart\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a devastating stab\", \"from\": 3885, \"to\": 3903}, {\"ngram\": \"the back\", \"from\": 3907, \"to\": 3915}, {\"ngram\": \"clean athletes\", \"from\": 3919, \"to\": 3933}, {\"ngram\": \"a deep betrayal\", \"from\": 3938, \"to\": 3953}, {\"ngram\": \"all the athletes\", \"from\": 3957, \"to\": 3973}, {\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 4004, \"to\": 4013}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"All of those with dirty hands in burying these positives and suppressing the voices of courageous whistleblowers must be held accountable to the fullest extent of the rules and law.\\\"\", \"from\": 4016, \"to\": 4199, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"dirty hands\", \"from\": 4035, \"to\": 4046}, {\"ngram\": \"these positives\", \"from\": 4058, \"to\": 4073}, {\"ngram\": \"the voices\", \"from\": 4090, \"to\": 4100}, {\"ngram\": \"courageous whistleblowers\", \"from\": 4104, \"to\": 4129}, {\"ngram\": \"the fullest extent\", \"from\": 4158, \"to\": 4176}, {\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 4180, \"to\": 4189}, {\"ngram\": \"law\", \"from\": 4194, \"to\": 4197}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Usada and the FBI are currently conducting an investigation of their own into Chinese doping under the authority of a US law, the 2019 Rodchenkov Anti-Doping Act, which allows nations to conduct cross-border investigations.\", \"from\": 4201, \"to\": 4424, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4215, \"end\": 4218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.675002389396906e-45, \"text\": \"FBI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.